# VuApp
An Android application built with Kotlin, following clean architecture, Hilt for dependency injection, Retrofit for networking, and MVVM architecture.

## Features

-  Login screen with ViewModel & Repository
-  Dashboard showing dynamic data from a REST API
-  Detail screen with full information display
-  Navigation between screens
-  Hilt for dependency injection
-  Retrofit for API integration
-  Unit tests using JUnit, MockK, and Mockito

##  Tech Stack

| Category        | Library/Tool                      |
|----------------|------------------------------------|
| Language        | Kotlin                            |
| Architecture    | MVVM, Clean Architecture           |
| Dependency DI   | Hilt (Dagger)                     |
| Networking      | Retrofit + Gson                   |
| UI Components   | Material Design, RecyclerView     |
| Testing         | JUnit, MockK, Mockito             |
| Version Control | Git + GitHub                      |

## ️ Project Structure

app/
├── di/                   # Dependency injection setup (Hilt modules)
├── repository/           # Repositories for data logic
├── viewmodel/            # ViewModels for Login and Dashboard
├── api/                  # Retrofit API service
├── model/                # Data models and wrappers
├── ui/                   # Activities: LoginActivity, DashboardActivity, DetailsActivity
├── res/                  # XML layouts, drawables, values
└── AndroidManifest.xml   # App configuration and permissions


##  Testing

-  Unit tests implemented for `LoginViewModel` and `DashboardRepository`
-  Test dependencies included:
  - `junit`
  - `mockk`
  - `mockito-core`
  - `kotlinx-coroutines-test`

##  Setup Instructions

1. Clone the repository:
   ```bash
   git clone https://github.com/kiidgaf/VuApp.git

2. Open the project in Android Studio

3. Sync Gradle and run the app on an emulator or physical device

